The baseline relies on NetworkX to build a full graph object, which adds considerable Python-level overhead.  
We can speed things up by bypassing NetworkX entirely and computing connected components with a lightweight Disjoint-Set Union (union-find) structure that runs in near-linear time on plain Python lists.

